<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF326A8EFA899B0C1D9BB90A" lastPageId="202" lastPageNumber="964" pageId="201" pageNumber="963" type="description">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF326A8EFA899B0C1D9BB90A" blockId="201.[1397,2604,3332,3487]" lastBlockId="202.[166,1376,296,1042]" lastPageId="202" lastPageNumber="964" pageId="201" pageNumber="963">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF326A8DFA899B0C1872B645" bold="true" box="[1397,1650,3413,3447]" pageId="201" pageNumber="963">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Forearm 39-2-41- 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF326A8DF8829B0C19D4B645" box="[1918,2004,3413,3447]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="201" pageNumber="963" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
. There are no other measurements available. Fur is long and dense. Dorsal pelage is dark brown, with hairs having blackish brown bases and paler chocolate-brown tips; venteris similar but slightly paler, with slightly paler hair tips. Ears are relatively short and narrow and taper toward rounded tips; tragusis long and narrow, with straight posterior margin. Wing attaches to base of outer toe. Skull has distinctly domed braincase; frontal depression is well developed; sagittal and lambdoidal crests are weakly developed; anteorbital bridge is wide; basal area of P? is one-third that of P* P? is relatively well developed and barely displaced from tooth row; and P,is developed and in tooth row.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
